          <div class="narm-review-text">This book does an excellent job of laying out the NARM model for working with developmental trauma. The two annotated session transcripts give us an inside look at each author's thought process — a peek behind the curtain. For therapists struggling with burnout or feeling stuck with clients, this chapter on the relational model will be incredibly useful.</div>
          <div class="narm-review-helpful">30 people found this helpful</div>
